<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-619-612  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 619 612.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  July 9 1990 v7 n26 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Natural-language 4GL supports any SQL database. (Tom Softwareintroduces Appx fourth generation language) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   TOM Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Appx (Program development software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFourth-Generation LanguagesProgram Development ToolsData Base LanguagesStructured Query Language.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Natural-language 4GL supports any SQL databaseandM;SEATTLE -- Tom Software has unveiled Appx, a natural fourth-generationlanguage that company officials said is designed to run in any SQL databaseenvironment.andM;&quot;Our system is in a natural language that allows you to build an appliationusing menus,&quot; said Louis Kern, the company's vice president of sales andmarketing.andP;  &quot;Other 4GLs force you to learn languages--laborious environmentsin which to work.andP;  [It] is much faster to write programs in our environment,&quot;he said.andM;Appx builds on and enhances Speed II, Tom Software's previously released 4GLenvironment.andM;Appx includes an application design facility and an interface that allowsusers to finish applications with little procedural coding by using Appx'sscreen-driven specification method, company officials said.andM;A data dictionary enables changes to be reflected automatically throughout anapplication.andP;  Database management tools perform file restructuring whenever arecord is modified.andP;  Appx also provides the ability to develop a prototype ofan appliation and then install it as the production system.andM;An Integrated Language Facility lets designers incorporate sophisticatedlogic to extend the specification capability or to call programs in othercomputer languages, officials said.andM;With the Appx query facility, users can generate customized queries andreports without using code.andM;&quot;We offer an interface to any SQL database.andP;  [Appx sits] on top of theirdatabase manager,&quot; Kern said.andP;  &quot;The design concept was to build [Appx] in amodular fashion to make it portable--it's written in C--and compatible withdata dictionaries from other relational databases.&quot;andM;The product is available now.andP;  Prices start at $3,500.andM;Tom Software Inc. can be contacted at 127 S.W.andP;  156th St., Seattle, WA 98166,(206) 246-7022.andO;</TEXT></DOC>